Include relevant screenshots of the application in action. For example, you can showcase the user interface for adding a new record, displaying existing records, updating records, and deleting records.

## Installation

Follow these steps to run the project locally:

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/ADILAYOUB/100_flutter_challange/tree/Day_11`
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd flutter-sqlite-crud-operation`
3. Install dependencies: `flutter pub get`
4. Run the application: `flutter run`

Make sure you have Flutter and Dart SDK installed on your local machine before running the application.

## Dependencies

- sqlite: ^0.5.7

These dependencies are used to interact with the SQLite database and display toast messages in the Flutter application. You can find more information about these packages in the [pub.dev](https://pub.dev) website.

